      "kwargs": {
        "content": "I attempted to run process `J09D`, but it cannot be executed right now due to a database connectivity issue.\n\nHere is what happened:\n\n1. Retrieved the process definition for `J09D` successfully:\n   - Create temp table `J09D_temp` from `decision_table` for TOURS starting with `J09D`\n   - Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - Apply rules:\n     - Per `HAUS`, if count(EQUNR) < 3 → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'KSA'`, else `EVU`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1` between 500 and 599 → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`\n   - Join with `EABLG` on `INSTALLATION`\n   - Join with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` on `EQUNR`\n   - For each ID: if sales data exists, keep sales / clear net; else keep net / clear sales\n   - Export CSV `J09D` with the specified columns\n   - Email to `meter.readings@evu.com`\n   - Drop temp table\n\n2. When trying to access the database:\n   - `get_db_schema()` → `Error no database connection`\n   - Test `run_sqlite_query(\"SELECT name, type FROM sqlite_master LIMIT 20;\")` → `Error no database connection`\n\nBecause there is **no active database connection**, I cannot:\n- Create the `J09D_temp` table\n- Run the joins and decision rules\n- Generate the CSV\n- Send the CSV to `meter.readings@evu.com`\n\n3. Escalation performed:\n- I have sent an incident email to `support@company.com` describing:\n  - Process ID: `J09D`\n  - Exact errors: “Error no database connection”\n  - That the process cannot proceed without DB access\n\nNext steps:\n- Once database connectivity is restored by support, the process can be re-run from the start to produce and send the `J09D` CSV as defined.\n- If you like, after you get confirmation that the DB is back up, ask me again to run process `J09D` and I will execute all the steps.",
